  "title": "Software Engineer (.Net/Sharepoint)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Software Engineer (.Net/Sharepoint)</strong></p><p> Support BAU operations for iNex and ALM SharePoint-based applications - </p><p>  Perform transition and migration activities, moving existing modules to cloud environments </p><p>- Design, develop, test, and maintain solutions using SharePoint (on-premise and online) </p><p>- Build and maintain CI/CD pipelines and manage work items using Azure DevOps </p><p>- Develop and integrate cloud components using Microsoft Azure (Logic Apps, Azure Functions) </p><p>- Implement automation and low-code solutions using UiPath and Microsoft Power Platform </p><p>- Conduct SharePoint migrations using ShareGate, ensuring data integrity and minimal downtime </p><p>- Troubleshoot application and infrastructure issues independently </p><p>- Collaborate with stakeholders to assess risks, impacts, and dependencies </p><p>- Provide clear communication on technical and business impacts of changes Qualifications Core Technologies: - </p><p>- - SharePoint (on premise & online) -</p><p> Microsoft Azure DevOps Services (including CI/CD pipelines development, work item customization) -</p><p> Microsoft Azure Cloud (LogicApps, Azure Functions) </p><p>- UiPath/Power Platform (Power Apps, Power Automate, Power Page) </p><p>- ShareGate for SharePoint migration. </p><p>Technical Competencies: </p><p>a) .NET, SPFx, PowerShell or Bash </p><p>- REST API - Pipeline YAML, XML, JSON Essential Abilities: </p><p>- Troubleshoot technical issues independently </p><p>- Assess and communicate business impacts effectively - Working experience in Singapore (preferred).</p>",
